<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="391" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="112.[178,1384,3095,3488]" pageId="112" pageNumber="391">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[180,395,3174,3207]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="112" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boylii">Peromyscus boylii</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Baird" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[525,590,3174,3207]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="112" pageNumber="391" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="boylii">boylii</taxonomicName>
species group. It once contained as many twelve subspecies, but several taxonomic revisions by R. D. Bradley and colleagues in 2014 and 2017 reduced the number to four. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
